claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: CONSORT flow diagram showing participant enrollment, allocation, follow-up, and re-randomization for Year 1 (2018–2019) and Year 2 (2019–2020) across four vaccine arms: cell-culture quadrivalent inactivated vaccine (cclIV4), recombinant-hemagglutinin influenza vaccine (RIV4), Fluzone IIV4, and Fluarix IIV4. It details numbers enrolled, completed visits at day 0, 1 month, and 6 months, and re-randomization into various vaccine sequences in Year 2. does not support the claim because this figure is solely a participant flow diagram and provides no information on antigenic match or strain composition for Flublok or any vaccine to WHO- or FDA-selected strains. Note: Limited to visible content; no strain details or matching data are presented in the figure.
